OL,3,CAlmost a third of Londoners have
OL,4,Cwitnessed 'violence and abuse while
OL,5,Cshopping'
OL,7,FNew figures reveal the extent of
OL,8,Fviolence or abuse against retail
OL,9,Fworkers with 32% of Londoners
OL,10,Fwitnessing attacks.
OL,12,FCases include racial and sexual abuse,
OL,13,Fphysical assault and threats with
OL,14,Fweapons while shopping, the poll by
OL,15,FOpinium for the British Retail
OL,16,FConsortium (BRC) found.
OL,18,FThe survey showed how rates varied
OL,19,Fsignificantly across the UK. The
OL,20,Flowest rate was in the East of England
OL,21,Fat 13%.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G1/6
