OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,407,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40605
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F406A1773857158
OL,3,CAlmost a third of Londoners have
OL,4,Cwitnessed 'violence and abuse while
OL,5,Cshopping'
OL,7,FBRC chief executive Helen Dickinson
OL,8,Fsaid: "For too many people, violence
OL,9,Fand abuse are now part of the shopping
OL,10,Fexperience. An incident might last
OL,11,Fseconds, but for workers and
OL,12,Fbystanders, the impact can last a
OL,13,Flifetime.
OL,15,F"The Crime and Policing Bill is an
OL,16,Fimportant step towards protecting
OL,17,Fretail workers and tackling crime. But
OL,18,Fas drafted, it falls short. Retail
OL,19,Fworkers in England and Wales deserve
OL,20,Fthe same protections as those in
OL,21,FScotland, including delivery drivers.
OL,26,@pD@GOUwD@AOU
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G5/6
